<refentry xml:id="function.msql-field-type" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
 <refnamediv>
  <refname>msql_field_type</refname>
  <refpurpose>Lit le type de champ mSQL</refpurpose>
 </refnamediv>
 <refsect1 role="description">
  &reftitle.description;
  <methodsynopsis>
   <type>string</type><methodname>msql_field_type</methodname>
   <methodparam><type>resource</type><parameter>result</parameter></methodparam>
   <methodparam><type>int</type><parameter>field_offset</parameter></methodparam>
  </methodsynopsis>
  <para>
   <function>msql_field_type</function> récupère le type du champ
   spécifié par son index.
  </para>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="parameters">
  &reftitle.parameters;
  <para>
   <variablelist>
    &msql.result.description;
    &msql.field-offset.req.description;
   </variablelist>
  </para>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="returnvalues">
  &reftitle.returnvalues;  
  <para>
   Le type du champ. Une valeur parmi <literal>int</literal>, 
   <literal>char</literal>, <literal>real</literal>, <literal>ident</literal>,
   <literal>null</literal> ou <literal>unknown</literal>.
   Cette fonction retourne &false; si une erreur survient.
  </para>
 </refsect1>
</refentry>

